</ul>

<h2>Tech stack confirmed</h2>
<div class="done">Replit as primary build and hosting management platform. GitHub for version control. Netlify for live hosting. Brevo for patient CRM and automations.</div>


<!-- ══════ APP ══════ -->
<h1>App — iOS / Android (future)</h1>
<hr class="rule">

<p>Not in scope for the August launch. For future reference:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>iOS App Store:</strong> requires an Apple Developer account (A$149/year). Replit supports a built-in Expo launch flow for iOS submission once ready.</li>
  <li><strong>Android / Google Play:</strong> not currently supported through Replit's publishing flow. Would need to be handled separately outside Replit when the time comes.</li>
  <li>Decision recommended: assess patient need and clinical workflow benefit before committing to app development — web-based approach (current) serves most use cases without App Store overhead.</li>
</ul>


